Zborowski v. City of New York. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. June 19, 1888.) Appeal from special term, New York county. Following Diefenthaler v. City of New York, ante, 912.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

Da/vidD. Acker, for plaintiff. G. L. Sterling, for defendant. Per Curiam.

The question involved upon this appeal seems to be the same as that which was disposed of in the case of Diefenthaler v. City of New York, ante, 912, (decided by this court in March, 1888.) The judgments and orders appealed from must be affirmed, with costs.
